<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="594" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1871,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1871,1896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="594">Etymology</emphasis>
. Melichar intended to name this species “ 
<taxonomicName box="[790,921,1871,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Lophopidae" genus="Binaluana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emarginata">emarginata</taxonomicName>
”, as written on the label and refers to the characters of frons (without carinae). We kept the name he had chosen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="8" pageNumber="594" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1871,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1943,1968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="594">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Coloration and pattern on dorsal view on the tegmina draw a whitish hastate leaf shaped figure. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1979,2004]" pageId="8" pageNumber="594">Description</emphasis>
. Total length 1.24 cm.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/243991/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="595" targetBox="[151,1436,159,1620]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1640,1724]" pageId="9" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,334,1640,1663]" pageId="9" pageNumber="595">FIGURES 42–47</emphasis>
. 
